---
/**
 * Slide 02 · The Bottleneck — a small team carries the surface area of a big
 * one, and historically had to triage most of it away. Sets up T03 + the fronts.
 */
const fronts = ["Sales / ABM", "Travel", "Events", "Grants", "Social"];
---

<section data-slot="02" data-variant="awm-v1" class="deck-section" style="justify-content: center;">
  <span class="deck-kicker">02 / 11</span>

  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <p class="deck-eyebrow mb-3">The bottleneck</p>
    <h2 class="deck-h1">
      A small team has the <span class="deck-gradient">surface area of a big one.</span>
    </h2>
  </div>

  <p class="deck-lede mt-2" style="max-width: 68ch;">
    Sales conversations, travel worth taking, conferences worth attending, grant
    pipelines, stakeholder relationships — the work is there whether or not the
    headcount is. Historically, the only lever was
    <span style="color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 600;"> triage: drop most of it on the floor.</span>
  </p>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 mt-3">
    <span class="deck-stat-label">Five fronts, all under-served at once</span>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
      {fronts.map((f) => <span class="deck-chip">{f}</span>)}
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="deck-lede mt-3" style="max-width: 64ch;">
    Overwhelm isn't just stress — it's a
    <span style="color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 600;"> ceiling on what's possible.</span>
    The next slide is how agents lift it.
  </p>
</section>
